module: a2-02
level: A2
sequence: 2
slug: the-dative-ii-nouns
version: '2.0'
title: The Dative II — Nouns
subtitle: Giving, Sending, and Showing
content_outline:
- section: Introduction / Вступ
  points:
  - Building on dative pronouns from M01 — recall «мені/тобі» as foundational examples;
    builds on A1-09 (Nominative Plural) for Dative Plural base
  - Indirect object concept (recipient of action) — frame as the "To/For" case for
    easier English-to-Ukrainian mapping (gave [to] mom, sent [to] dad)
  - Ukrainian overview of recipients — include typical contexts like «Дідусеві вісімдесят
    років» to introduce age expression (Standard §4.2.2.3)
- section: Presentation
  points:
  - 'Masculine endings (-ові/-у) — contrast «студентові» and «студенту»; learner error:
    avoid confusion with Accusative/Genitive; learner error: mixing gender endings
    (e.g. giving Masc -у to Fem nouns)'
  - 'Feminine endings (-і) with consonant changes — focus on shifts: г-з (нога-нозі),
    к-ц (рука-руці), х-с (муха-мусі) for phonetic euphony'
  - Neuter and Plural endings — emphasize -ам for plurals, building on A1 Nominative
    Plural knowledge
  - 'Dative-hungry verbs — focus on high-frequency social verbs like «телефонувати»
    (call mom/doctor), «допомагати» (help parents/friend), «дарувати» (give flowers/joy);
    learner error: using Accusative for help/call (e.g. «допомагати маму» instead
    of «мамі»)'
- section: Practice
  points:
  - Reading and sentence transformation — use "Gift Etiquette" context (odd number
    of flowers for living, avoid yellow for romance) to practice «дарувати квіти мамі»
- section: Dialogues
  points:
  - Mini-dialogues in context — include "Angel Day" (Name Day) greetings «Вітаю з
    Днем ангела!» and gift-giving scenarios for the «іменинник»
  - Cultural note context — discuss taboo gifts (sharp objects, watches) in a dialogue
    where characters 'buy' the gift for a coin to avoid bad luck
vocabulary_hints:
  required:
  - 'давати (to give) — collocations: «давати пораду» (give advice), «давати відповідь»
    (give answer), «давати слово» (give word/promise)'
  - 'дарувати (to gift) — collocations: «дарувати квіти» (give flowers), «дарувати
    радість» (bring joy), «дарувати подарунок» (give a gift); cultural hook: odd number
    for the living!'
  - посилати (to send) — generic "to send" (e.g., a courier)
  - 'надсилати (to send) — digital/post: «надсилати листа» (send a letter), «надсилати
    повідомлення» (send a message)'
  - показувати (to show) — showing the way or a gift to a recipient
  - пояснювати (to explain) — «пояснювати правила» (explain rules), «пояснювати дорогу»
    (explain the way), «пояснювати причину» (explain reason)
  - розповідати (to tell) — telling a story or news to someone
  - 'допомагати (to help) — collocations: «допомагати батькам» (help parents), «допомагати
    у навчанні» (help with studies); learner error: use Dative («допомагати мамі»),
    NOT Accusative («маму»)'
  - заважати (to bother) — bothering or hindering someone
  - личити (to suit) — clothing/style suiting someone
  - підходити (to suit) — something being suitable for someone
  - вистачати (to be enough) — being sufficient for someone
  - бракувати (to lack) — something missing/lacking for someone
  - відповідати (to answer) — answering to a person or group
  - 'телефонувати (to call) — collocations: «телефонувати мамі» (call mom), «телефонувати
    лікарю» (call doctor); learner error: use Dative («телефонувати директору»), NOT
    Accusative; distinct from «кликати»'
  recommended:
  - шкодити (to harm) — causing harm to someone/something
  - вірити (to believe) — believing someone
  - довіряти (to trust) — trusting someone
  - радити (to advise) — giving advice to someone
  - дозволяти (to allow) — allowing/permitting someone
activity_hints:
- type: fill-in
  focus: Add dative endings to nouns
  items: 15+
- type: quiz
  focus: Form dative from nominative
  items: 12+
- type: match-up
  focus: Verb + typical dative object pairs
  items: 10+
- type: fill-in
  focus: Complete sentences with correct dative noun
  items: 10+
- type: quiz
  focus: Choose correct dative ending by gender
  items: 10+
focus: grammar
pedagogy: PPP
prerequisites:
- a2-01 (Dative pronouns)
- A1 noun gender recognition
- A1 accusative case
connects_to:
- a2-03 (Dative Verbs)
- a2-04 (Instrumental I)
- a2-09 (All Cases Practice)
objectives:
- Learner can form dative case endings for masculine nouns
- Learner can form dative case endings for feminine and neuter nouns
- Learner can form dative plural endings
- Learner can use dative nouns with common verbs
grammar:
- dative noun endings
- masculine dative (-ові/-у)
- feminine dative (-і)
- neuter dative (-у/-ові)
- plural dative (-ам)
module_type: grammar
sources:
- name: Ukrainian State Standard 2024 - Noun Declension
  url: https://mon.gov.ua/
  type: reference
  notes: Complete dative endings for all noun genders
- name: Ukrainian Grammar Tables
  url: https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/Відмінювання_іменників
  type: reference
  notes: Declension patterns and exceptions
immersion: 50-60% Ukrainian
phase: A2.1
persona:
  voice: Encouraging Cultural Guide
  role: Philanthropist
word_target: 3000
